console.log("Portfolio loaded");

Commit and push to GitHub
cd C:\project1
git add -A
git commit -m "init static site"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

Create the Vercel project (static site)

Vercel → Add New → Project → select ajitheee/portfolio1

Framework Preset: Other (Static)

Build Command: (leave empty)

Output Directory: (leave empty or .)

Root Directory: only set if your files are in a subfolder

Click Deploy, then set Settings → Git → Production Branch = main

Quick checks

Must have index.html at the chosen root (otherwise Vercel shows 404).

Use relative paths in HTML (e.g., ./assets/styles.css).

If you run ls now and paste the list you see in C:\project1, I’ll confirm the exact Vercel settings for your layout.


  cd C:\project1
git pull origin main --rebase
2) Turn your code into the homepage file
If portfoliocode.txt contains your HTML, rename it to index.html:

powershell
Copy code
Rename-Item .\portfoliocode.txt index.html
(That CRLF warning you saw earlier is normal on Windows—safe to ignore.)

3) Commit and push
powershell
Copy code
git add -A
git commit -m "rename: portfoliocode.txt -> index.html"
git push -u origin main
